    "recap_headline": "University of Connecticut Athletics",
    "recap_text": "PORTLAND, Ore.\n- The UConn baseball team (8-11) took a step back this weekend with a series loss to Portland (11-8) after dropping the deciding game, 5-3, on Sunday afternoon at Joe Etzel Field.\nTied 3-3 in the bottom of the seventh, redshirt freshman\nDrew Smith\npitched out of a first and second two out jam with a great catch in foul ground by right fielder\nCam Righi\nand a ground out to second base.\nWith momentum,\nTyler Minick\nlined a double to right center, his third hit of the day, to lead off the frame. After a strikeout to\nJackson Marshall\n,\nChris Polemeni\nwalked to place runners at first and second.\nEvan Menzel\nfollowed with a fly out to right to move MInick to third with two outs.\nWith the Huskies 1-9 with runners in scoring position on the day, the Huskies tried to sneak it in the run from third but the play was sniffed out and Minick was tagged out in a rundown between third and home.\nPortland responded with a single to right and a controversial hit by pitch to place runners at first and second. After a sacrifice bunt, a ground ball to second baseman\nEvan Menzel\ntook his momentum towards the outfield and his off balance throw to the plate was late. The Pilots scratched across another run on a ground out to short to take a 5-3 lead. The Huskies went down quietly in the ninth to drop four of thier last five games since reaching the .500 mark (7-7).\nJackson Marshall\ngave UConn an early lead with a first inning home run to center field, his team-leading sixth of the season.\nAfter Portland took a 3-2 in the fifth,\nEvan Menzel\nand the Huskies responded with an RBI single to tie the game in the sixth, 3-3.\nOliver Pudvar\npitched a season-high 6.1 innings of three-run ball with five strikeouts.\nMarshall and Polemeni each recorded multi-hit efforts along with Minick.\nNext up, the Huskies continue their spring break trip with a midweek contest at the University of California in Berkeley, Calif. on Tuesday, March 17 at 9 p.m. ET / 6 p.m. PT."
  },
